    Choosing the right Tech business name

    Need help deciding? Build a standout brand with our naming best practices.

    Short and simple

    Choose a name that’s easy to type so customers can find you. Avoid odd or complicated spellings.

    Easy to pronounce

    People are more likely to remember a name that’s effortlessly pronounced and understood.

    Reflects your brand

    A good name represents your business and is easily associated with the products or services you offer.

    Unique and available

    Make sure your business name stands out and is not already used by a competitor in your category.

    Looking for more naming tips?

    Read our blog guide on how to craft a memorable brand name of your own.

    Frequently asked questions

    Yes, Shopify's Tech business name generator is free to use. You can generate numerous name ideas for your Tech business without any cost. You can also other free tools from Shopify.

    The free Tech business name generator provides instant suggestions in three simple steps:

    • Think of a word that best describes your Tech brand or business
    • Enter it into the name generator field
    • Click on the “Generate names” button

    That’s it! You now have a list of creative name suggestions tailored for Tech businesses to select from or use as inspiration

    Choosing the right name for your Tech business is crucial. Here are some general tips:

    • Keep it Memorable: Easy to recall, pronounce, and spell.
    • Reflect Your Brand: Does it convey the essence of your Tech offerings?
    • Check Availability: Ensure the domain name and social media handles are free.
    • Consider Your Target Audience: Will it resonate with potential customers for Tech products/services?
    • Future-Proof It: Will it still be relevant as your Tech business grows?

    A good Tech brand name should ideally be:

    • Unique & Distinctive: Stands out from competitors in the Tech space.
    • Relevant: Clearly hints at what your Tech business offers or its core values.
    • Easy to Remember & Pronounce: Facilitates word-of-mouth marketing.
    • Universal: The brand name makes sense across different languages.
    • Scalable: Allows your Tech brand to grow without needing a rename.

    Popular Tech brand names include:

    • Microsoft
    • Google
    • Apple
    • IBM
    • Dell Technologies
    • Cisco

    Once you have some Tech business name ideas, it's important to check their availability. Here's what we recommend:

    1. Domain Name Availability: Our business name generator allows you to check domain availability for your chosen Tech names directly. You can also use Shopify's free domain name generator tool or other domain registrars to see if the .com or other desired domain extensions are available
    2. Social Media Handles: Search for your desired Tech name on major social media platforms like Instagram, Facebook, X (formerly Twitter), TikTok, and Pinterest to see if the username is available.
    3. Trademark Search: Conduct a search on official trademark databases (e.g., USPTO in the US, CIPO in Canada, EUIPO in Europe) to ensure your Tech name isn't already trademarked by another business, in your industry or a related one.
    4. General Web Search: Perform a web search for your desired Tech name to see if other businesses are using similar names

    Congratulations on finding a great name for your Tech business! Choosing a name is an exciting first step. Here’s a general guide on what to do next:

    • Secure Your Domain Name: This is often the most immediate step. Check if the domain name corresponding to your chosen Tech name is available (e.g., your-tech-name.com). You can usually do this through Shopify’s free domain name generator tool or other domain registrars. Act fast to claim it.
    • Register Your Business: Make your Tech business official by registering it according to your local, state/provincial, and national legal requirements. This might involve choosing a business structure (e.g., sole proprietorship, LLC, corporation) and obtaining any necessary licenses or permits for your Tech industry.
    • Develop Your Brand Identity:
      • Logo: Create a logo that represents your Tech brand. Shopify has a free logo maker tool you can use.
      • Brand Style: Think about your brand colors, fonts, and overall visual style that will appeal to your target audience for Tech products/services.
    • Build Your Online Presence:
      • Shopify Store: Start building your online store. Shopify provides all the tools you need to create a professional website for your Tech business, list products/services, and accept payments.
      • Social Media: Secure social media handles on platforms relevant to your Tech business (e.g., Instagram, Facebook, TikTok, Pinterest, LinkedIn).
    • Plan Your Products/Services and Operations Next, finalize your Tech product line or service offerings. Think about sourcing, inventory (if applicable), pricing, and shipping for your Tech business.
    • Create a Business Plan: Outline your goals, target market for your Tech business, marketing strategies, and financial projections.
    • Start Marketing: Begin thinking about how you'll market your new Tech business and attract your first customers.

    You've named your business—congrats! Once you've secured your website domain with our domain name generator (tip: aim for something as close to your business name as possible), it’s time to set up your Tech store on Shopify.

    Once you're set on a name, start your free trial and select an online store theme that brings your brand to life.

    Make it easy for customers to find your products by adding different sales channels. For help promoting your brand, try our free marketing tools and apps. And for plenty of guides and inspiration, check out our blog or consult the Shopify community for answers to your questions.
